%% Diagram: Signed URL / signed cookie flow — sign at origin, verify at edge
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User
    participant App as Origin app\n(holds private key)
    participant Edge as CDN edge PoP\n(holds public key /\nkey group)
    participant Bucket as Origin storage

    User->>App: GET /watch/123 (authenticated)
    Note over App: Build policy:\nresource, expiry, IP, key-id
    App->>App: Sign(policy, privateKey)\nRSA-2048 / ECDSA-P256\nSHA-256
    App-->>User: 302 → cdn.example.com/...\n?Signature=...&Key-Pair-Id=...&Expires=...

    User->>Edge: GET signed URL
    Note over Edge: Lookup public key by Key-Pair-Id\nin trusted key group
    Edge->>Edge: Verify signature, expiry,\noptional IP / referrer policy
    alt Valid + cache hit
        Edge-->>User: 200 + cached bytes
    else Valid + cache miss
        Edge->>Bucket: Authenticated origin pull
        Bucket-->>Edge: 200 bytes
        Edge-->>User: 200 bytes (cached)
    else Invalid or expired
        Edge-->>User: 403 Forbidden
        Note over Edge: Never reaches origin
    end
